{{about|an algorithm|Israeli food corporation|Osem (company)}}
In [[mathematical optimization]], the '''ordered subset expectation maximization''' (OSEM) method <!-- NOT algorithm -->  is an [[iterative method]] that is used in [[computed tomography]].

In applications in [[medical imaging]], the OSEM method is used  for [[positron emission tomography]], for [[single photon emission computed tomography]], and for [[Computed tomography|X-ray computed tomography]].

The OSEM method is related to the [[expectation maximization]] (EM) method of statistics. The OSEM method is also related to methods of [[filtered back projection]].

