'''Worksafe''' is an agency within the [[Department of Commerce (Western Australia)|Department of Commerce]], which is part of the [[Government of Western Australia|state government]], responsible for the administration of the ''Occupational Safety and Health Act of 1984''.<ref>{{cite web| url=http://www.slp.wa.gov.au/legislation/statutes.nsf/main_mrtitle_650_homepage.html|title=Occupational Safety and Health Act of 1984|year=2012|accessdate=23 April 2013|publisher=[[Government of Western Australia]]}}</ref>  
There are also agencies in other states of Australia, and at a national level with similar names and objectives<ref>for example {{cite web |url=http://www.worksafe.vic.gov.au/|title=Worksafe Victoria|year=2012|accessdate=23 April 2013|publisher=[[Government of Victoria]] }} {{cite web| url=http://www.worksafe.nt.gov.au/home.aspx|title=Worksafe Northern Territory|year=2012|accessdate=23 April 2013|publisher=[[Government of Northern Territory]]}}, {{cite web| url=http://www.worksafe.com.au/|title= Workplace Safety Australia|year=2012|accessdate=23 April 2013|publisher=[[Government of Australia]] }}</ref>

The principal objective of the act and the division is to secure the safety and health of people in the workplace.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.commerce.wa.gov.au/worksafe/|title=WorkSafe WA|year=2012|accessdate=23 April 2013|publisher=[[Government of Western Australia]]}}</ref>

